###############################################################################

  This document describes the usage of runmake, the Trilinos make utility.
  
  The runmake utility provides a standard way to compile Trilinos source and
  generate results.  This simplifies the process of automating Trilinos testing
  when combined with other utilities.
  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I.  Prerequisites

  In order for the make utility to work, you must have the following in place:
  
    1. You must have a correctly configured build directory.
       
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
II.  Execution

  To execute the Trilinos make utility, simply type:
  
    cd /PATH/TO/Trilinos/commonTools/test/utilities/
    perl runmake --help
            
  Refer to this help output for the most up-to-date information on usage and
  available options.  (You can use "./" instead of "perl " if your system's
  perl interpreter resides at /usr/bin/perl)
  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
III.  Make Results File

  The results of the make attempt will be placed in the specified output
  directory and will be named according to the following scheme:
  
    YR-MO-DA_HR.MN.SE-make.txt
  
  The make results file will consist of the following:
  
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------------+
  |HOST_NAME            = beowulf
  |DNS_NAME             = cs.csbsju.edu
  |IP_ADDRESS           = 127.0.0.1 
  |OPERATING_SYSTEM     = GNU/Linux
  |KERNEL_NAME          = Linux
  |KERNEL_RELEASE       = 2.6.10-beowulf
  |KERNEL_VERSION       = #1 Sat Jan 22 23:03:17 CST 2005
  |PROCESSOR            = AMD Athlon(tm) 
  |MACHINE_HARDWARE     = i686
  |HARDWARE_PLATFORM    = AuthenticAMD
  |
  |TRILINOS_DIR         = /common/TrilinosTestHarness/runtests/Trilinos/
  |BRANCH_TAG           = development
  |
  |BUILD_DIR            = /common/TrilinosTestHarness/runtests/Trilinos/MPI/
  |MAKE_COMMAND         = make -j4
  |
  |START_TIME           = 05-04-16 20:33:26
  |STOP_TIME            = 05-04-16 20:33:56
  |RUN_TIME             = 30 seconds
  |
  |EXIT_STATUS          = 0
  |RESULT               = pass
  |
  |BROKEN_PACKAGE       = NONE
  |
  |BEGIN_MAKE_OUTPUT
  |
  |...
  |
  |END_MAKE_OUTPUT
  |
  +---------------------------------------------------------------------------+

